1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,740
[All characters, behaviors, locations,
organizations, professions, and events

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:07,490
shown in this series are entirely fictional,
created solely for entertainment purposes,

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:11,250
with no intention of instructing
or endorsing any kind of behaviors;

4
00:00:11,270 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:21,200
But I can still remember
what happened that night so vividly.

6
00:00:21,790 --> 00:00:23,480
It was just a one-night stand!

7
00:00:23,580 --> 00:00:25,130
We go our separate ways
after the night ends!

8
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:27,670
I'm not hooking up
with the same person twice.

9
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:30,520
Good. That's clear.

10
00:00:31,180 --> 00:00:32,150
I've just realized

11
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,180
what Gen Zers are like.

12
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:36,380
Did the rain make you sleep so well?

13
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:38,710
Mm.

14
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:41,110
Yes.

15
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:41,810
But...

16
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,160
Can you give me 10 more minutes?

17
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:45,050
- Okay.
- I'll...

18
00:02:45,079 --> 00:02:47,480
Do hurry, though,
or else you'll miss breakfast.

19
00:02:47,820 --> 00:02:49,090
I'll wait for you at the cafeteria.

20
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:59,560
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

21
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:03,620
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

22
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:09,010
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

23
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:12,870
♫Then today, I got you near♫

24
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:17,660
♫You made my heart drift away,♫

25
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,649
♫Lost in your gaze♫

26
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:23,160
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

27
00:04:23,190 --> 00:04:28,640
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it's more than one night?♫

28
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:32,250
♫Let's change one night into♫

29
00:04:32,290 --> 00:04:34,070
♫Something more, alright♫

30
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:37,220
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

31
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:43,100
♫Wanna give this a try, just let me get inside?♫

32
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:49,330
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

33
00:04:49,540 --> 00:04:53,880
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

34
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:18,860
I'm here to see Sila.

35
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,680
Oh, he is not here, I am afraid.

36
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,880
He went out with Mr. Chakkrit.

37
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:25,990
Where were they off to?

38
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:29,700
Mr. Chakkrit did not inform us,

39
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:31,740
but they had left since this morning.

40
00:05:32,810 --> 00:05:34,380
I will be waiting for them upstairs, then.

41
00:05:35,110 --> 00:05:36,909
Please wait.

42
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:42,340
Mr. Sila does not allow visitors
to enter upstairs without his permission.

43
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,610
- Please...
- "Visitors"?

44
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,770
I'm like a sister to him at this point.

45
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,800
So...

46
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,400
Ms. Kanokwan,

47
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,960
you must be new here, correct?

48
00:05:52,010 --> 00:05:53,909
- That is why...
- I am here for Sila.

49
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:56,300
We are here to discuss businesses.

50
00:05:59,020 --> 00:05:59,710
Hey!

51
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,120
Sorry?

52
00:06:03,450 --> 00:06:05,100
Gale! It's you, isn't it?

53
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:07,120
Remember me?

54
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:09,390
You...

55
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:11,800
Who are you again?

56
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,110
I'm Mueanphae.

57
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:16,090
We went to the same fashion school.

58
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:18,670
FA Paris, 34th Batch.

59
00:06:18,810 --> 00:06:19,520
Remember?

60
00:06:23,590 --> 00:06:25,060
- We were in the same batch, too?
- Paris...

61
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:26,600
Mm.

62
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:28,830
Hm?

63
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:35,000
Muean...phae?

64
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,700
Excuse me.

65
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:49,180
I have informed Mr. Sila.

66
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:53,000
He says you can wait for him in his room.

67
00:06:53,030 --> 00:06:55,040
He will join you when he arrives.

68
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:55,780
Understood.

69
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:57,010
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

70
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:58,580
Shall we head upstairs together?

71
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:00,010
Mm.

72
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,720
Do you remember now?

73
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:08,690
[Phusangdao Group]

74
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,300
Your draft is decent, Gale.

75
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:13,740
But I'm not certain about the details.

76
00:07:14,110 --> 00:07:15,970
I don't have a head for fashion.

77
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:21,480
At any rate, I suggest
you two have a discussion,

78
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,600
okay?

79
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,880
Oh, and Ms. Wipa,
please discuss with our team

80
00:07:26,910 --> 00:07:29,040
where we might be able to
incorporate this part.

81
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,520
No problem, Mr. Sila.

82
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:33,120
I will inform you directly
if there are any updates, Ms. Gale.

83
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,880
Thank you very much, Ms. Wipa.

84
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,100
I hope this does not trouble you.

85
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:36,680
Understood.

86
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,640
Oh, Gale, can you give me your LINE ID?

87
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,400
It's fairly busy right around the vicinity,

88
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:45,820
so you might need to schedule a visit.

89
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,440
Sure.

90
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:48,720
No problem.

91
00:07:53,590 --> 00:07:54,880
Thank you.

92
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,040
It's a pleasure working with you.

93
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,200
I shall be your good assistant.

94
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:01,520
Right.

95
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:04,080
I have to take my leave now, Sila.

96
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,920
Oh.

97
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,170
See you.

98
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:06,880
Right.

99
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,700
See you soon.

100
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,590
Let me escort you downstairs.

101
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:11,270
Okay.

102
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,180
Follow me.

103
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:15,800
Thank you.

104
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:18,560
You can breathe, you know?

105
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:20,680
You were stiff as a rock.

106
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:23,300
Ow!

107
00:08:23,450 --> 00:08:24,790
Why did you hit me? That hurt.

108
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,840
You'll ruin it for me.

109
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:28,050
Play it cool.

110
00:08:29,650 --> 00:08:31,060
You're the one who has to play it cool.

111
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,470
She's your long-time crush, isn't she?

112
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,890
I think the time has come.

113
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,600
Isn't being a crush more than enough?

114
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,610
I'm afraid I'll do
something that crosses the line.

115
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,240
I don't want things to be awkward.

116
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,900
Don't take it that way.

117
00:08:46,770 --> 00:08:48,360
If the opportunity presents itself,

118
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:49,200
go and seize it.

119
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:49,920
Oh!

120
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,080
And...

121
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,000
How's Aunt?

122
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:54,280
Is she doing well?

123
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:58,350
My mother's fine.

124
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,980
She's been into growing orchids lately.

125
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,310
She watches videos about it all day long.

126
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:05,690
Such a classic 'old person' hobby, isn't it?

127
00:09:06,830 --> 00:09:07,880
That's great, though.

128
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,050
Her mind must be at ease now,

129
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:12,720
seeing how far you've grown.

130
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:13,490
Hey.

131
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,920
I'm not a kid anymore.

132
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,400
I'm this old, you see.

133
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,120
No, I'm not talking about your age.

134
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,760
I mean,

135
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,520
your duties.

136
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:25,520
You have so many matters to take care of,

137
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,480
and still managed them well, despite that.

138
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,640
That's what I mean.

139
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,200
It's your first day here,

140
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,720
how did you know I've been doing well?

141
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:37,200
You're flattering me too much, you know?

142
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:38,960
I am not.

143
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:45,410
I could tell from the vibes
when I arrived here.

144
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,440
I believe...

145
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:53,600
your father should be able to feel it, too.

146
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:56,840
Right now,

147
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:03,800
You've done everything so well.

148
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,960
I'm still trying, though.

149
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:26,800
I want everyone here to be happy.

150
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:37,800
Hello.

151
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,640
How is it? Isn't this beautiful?

152
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,040
It is.

153
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:45,270
But it's a bit tough to get around.

154
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:48,720
Well, you're wearing high heels.

155
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,080
My mistake, I guess.

156
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,160
Whoa!

157
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:01,680
I haven't been here for a few years.

158
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,580
Has the farm expanded this much?

159
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:06,320
There are a lot more workers as well.

160
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,240
Sila, you oversee everything here yourself?

161
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,400
I do, mostly.

162
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:15,590
But recently, I've often left it to
Chakkrit and Wipa,

163
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,390
as I've been busy with documents
for the business partner.

164
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
The business partner?

165
00:11:22,030 --> 00:11:23,120
Oh.

166
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:26,480
You mean K Group, the one you'll close
the deals with at the Northern Summit Event?

167
00:11:26,730 --> 00:11:27,500
Exactly.

168
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:30,060
The deal is about tea leaf export.

169
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:32,380
That is why things are the way they are now.

170
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:35,240
Every worker here is busy
with the tea leaves right now.

171
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,840
Mm.

172
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,390
Is there anything I can help with?

173
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,480
Do you know how to pick tea leaves?

174
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,690
I'm talking about your paperwork

175
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,960
or contacting clients overseas.

176
00:11:49,090 --> 00:11:51,080
Picking tea leaves is not an easy task.

177
00:11:51,490 --> 00:11:53,680
Who could possibly learn
to do it in a day or two?

178
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,080
There is one.

179
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,400
Don't talk nonsense. Let's get it done.

180
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:12,590
Oh, Gale.

181
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:15,240
We are currently producing tea wine,
our newest product.

182
00:12:15,530 --> 00:12:16,600
Would you like to try a bottle?

183
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,360
I'll have it served in your room.

184
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:19,330
You can?

185
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,360
Of course.

186
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,520
Sure thing.

187
00:12:21,930 --> 00:12:24,080
It'll make me sleep soundly tonight.

188
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:25,040
Sure.

189
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,800
Are there vegetable patches
at the end of the farm?

190
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:33,470
Sila.

191
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,400
Sila.

192
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,720
Sila!

193
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,440
Huh?

194
00:12:48,890 --> 00:12:49,580
Oh.

195
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:52,640
Yes, they're still there, like always.

196
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,580
Would you like a pain relief patch?

197
00:12:59,810 --> 00:13:00,480
What?

198
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:03,520
I've seen you craning your neck so much

199
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,160
that you're starting
to look like a giraffe.

200
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:06,610
I was worried you'd be in pain.

201
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:08,180
Hey, you're quite a blabbermouth.

202
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:09,640
If you don't shut it, I’m gonna...

203
00:13:10,650 --> 00:13:12,630
If you're that worried, why don't you
pull up your pant legs and go help him...

204
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:13,800
There!

205
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,140
Keep raving.

206
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:18,280
I'm going to work.

207
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,190
What a waste of time talking to you.

208
00:13:20,230 --> 00:13:20,680
Ow...

209
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,360
What's going on, Chakkrit?

210
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,600
Here's the deal, Ms. Gale...

211
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:34,640
Lately,

212
00:13:34,810 --> 00:13:36,160
Boss has been showing up a lot.

213
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,490
Ooh!

214
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,600
He's probably worried about someone here.

215
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:43,400
These kids.

216
00:13:43,610 --> 00:13:45,170
Don't just play around.

217
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:47,030
Focus on your work for once,

218
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:50,000
and teach Saitharn how to do it, too.

219
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:52,080
He's already
been taught everything earlier.

220
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:53,190
Yeah.

221
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,510
Saitharn is already doing great.

222
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,080
There's no need to teach him more.

223
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:58,400
It's not like he's pulling out
the whole root or anything.

224
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,480
Right?

225
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,200
- Whoa!!
- Whoa!

226
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,320
It's fine.

227
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,170
- It's okay.
- This is fine.

228
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:06,440
Don't worry about it.

229
00:14:06,610 --> 00:14:07,350
Let's keep going.

230
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:09,200
- Here, here, let's try again.
- You're already doing great.

231
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,390
- Don't mind it.
- It's fine.

232
00:14:10,430 --> 00:14:11,460
Keep going.

233
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:12,800
Come here.

234
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:14,980
Let's go.

235
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:16,890
Go where?

236
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:18,420
I'm not going.

237
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:19,280
Let's go.

238
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:31,110
Uh?

239
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:32,970
What?

240
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:34,220
Wait...

241
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:37,000
Why not put it properly on the plate?

242
00:14:37,170 --> 00:14:39,400
You're really clueless.
It's better this way.

243
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:46,680
Uh...

244
00:14:53,690 --> 00:14:54,380
My, my!

245
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,520
I'm gonna give
the desserts out to my friends.

246
00:14:59,040 --> 00:14:59,610
What are you looking at?

247
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:01,260
You looked at me first!

248
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,080
When did I?!

249
00:15:02,370 --> 00:15:03,600
You're doing it right now!

250
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,300
Jeez, why am I so sore today?

251
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,490
This is so heavy.

252
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:18,760
What are you doing?!
Give me back my basket!

253
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,490
Just follow me
and stop blabbering!

254
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,160
Jeez, you crazy!

255
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:24,770
What the hell is he up to?

256
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:45,800
[Chakkrit sent you a photo]

257
00:15:45,830 --> 00:15:48,190
[Chakkrit sent you a photo]

258
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:05,720
[Morning, what should we eat today?]

259
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,380
Let's go.

260
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:32,100
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

261
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,300
Don't drive too fast, please.
I'm scared.

262
00:16:35,710 --> 00:16:36,930
Mok, are you good?

263
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:38,050
I am.

264
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,580
This is easy peasy.

265
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,340
Yahoo!

266
00:16:58,350 --> 00:16:58,890
Whoa.

267
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,890
Oh, yes!

268
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:08,400
Darn, that's a lot.

269
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:10,130
Come here, come here.

270
00:17:10,170 --> 00:17:13,880
Yay!

271
00:17:22,490 --> 00:17:23,760
You're getting better.

272
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,120
Hi.

273
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,080
Hello.

274
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,200
Hello.

275
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,180
Oh, Boss.

276
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,200
You missed lunch,

277
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,980
but Auntie Nong has packed
some food in a tiffin box for you.

278
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:44,160
Why do you eat so early today?

279
00:17:44,420 --> 00:17:46,080
Oh, we've got that boy's help,

280
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,120
so we got it done a little faster.

281
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:48,220
We hit the quota,

282
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:50,000
so we got to take an early lunch break.

283
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,410
We will dry the tea leaves this afternoon.

284
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:54,100
- Oh, okay.
- Don't forget your lunch, Boss.

285
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:54,860
Okay, okay.

286
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:56,480
- Bye, Boss.
- Bye now.

287
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:20,600
You're pretty good.

288
00:18:21,190 --> 00:18:24,220
Just a short class with AI
and you already know how to harvest tea leaves.

289
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,440
How do you know?

290
00:18:34,290 --> 00:18:34,880
Here.

291
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:37,440
Hey!

292
00:18:39,170 --> 00:18:41,520
Hey, I went into hiding for that.

293
00:18:41,650 --> 00:18:42,880
What gives you the right to record me?

294
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,640
I'm gonna sue you for violating my privacy!

295
00:18:44,810 --> 00:18:46,560
Hey, are you really gonna sue me?

296
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:48,960
This video is a top pick.

297
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,260
What do you mean by "top pick"?

298
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:56,880
Picking tea leaves.

299
00:18:57,150 --> 00:18:59,080
- Nonsense!
- Hey, watch your mouth,

300
00:18:59,370 --> 00:19:01,480
or else I'm gonna leak
this video everywhere.

301
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:03,200
Hey, give it to me!

302
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:04,530
Give it to me. I'm deleting the video.

303
00:19:04,570 --> 00:19:05,030
Take it.

304
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:05,560
Hey.

305
00:19:05,990 --> 00:19:06,600
Hey!

306
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:07,880
Hey.

307
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:09,030
Hey, give it to me.

308
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:10,420
Give it to me.

309
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:11,310
Ouch!

310
00:19:15,810 --> 00:19:16,320
Uh...

311
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:18,440
You...

312
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:19,280
-There!
- Ow!

313
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:20,440
- Ow, you!
- There!

314
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:22,610
- There!
- Hey, you're making a mess.

315
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,420
You totally saw that I was falling.

316
00:19:24,870 --> 00:19:26,200
Did you ever think to help?

317
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:30,430
Well, I was shocked
that you suddenly went in for a hug...

318
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,000
Come on.

319
00:19:34,330 --> 00:19:35,160
Hurry.

320
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:43,670
Whoa!

321
00:20:23,210 --> 00:20:24,200
There!

322
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:27,710
Jeez!

323
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:29,230
Why is your hand so salty?

324
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,290
Nam prik nam poo.

325
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,400
I just put the plate away

326
00:20:33,450 --> 00:20:34,490
and never got to wash my hands.

327
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:34,990
Ugh!

328
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:39,120
Hey...

329
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:41,680
You!

330
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:52,200
Are you not going to have lunch, Miss?

331
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:53,080
Oh.

332
00:20:54,260 --> 00:20:55,210
Sure.

333
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:02,600
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

334
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:11,080
- Excuse me.
- Right.

335
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:16,690
Going somewhere again?

336
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:18,960
I'm heading to Phusangdao Farm.

337
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:24,960
You've been going there quite often recently.

338
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:27,760
What business do you have there?

339
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:31,240
I've been helping Gale with clothing

340
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:33,800
for the fashion show at the Northern Summit.

341
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:36,010
They want the materials from our farm.

342
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:39,010
Gale?

343
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:41,710
Sila's relative?

344
00:21:42,330 --> 00:21:42,980
Yes.

345
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,480
Are you close to her?

346
00:21:48,430 --> 00:21:50,200
Not now, but...

347
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:52,360
I think we'll get closer soon.

348
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,290
She seems like a nice person.

349
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,400
She's also talented.

350
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:58,080
On top of that,

351
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,960
she has a strong fashion sense.

352
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,790
Discuss only work-related matters with her.

353
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,280
Don't get that much closer.

354
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,880
Why don't you want me to be closer to her?

355
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,780
She's probably just like him.

356
00:22:18,990 --> 00:22:21,160
Have you forgotten what happened to me?

357
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,680
Remember how close Sila and I were?

358
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:29,680
He cut ties with our family

359
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,520
by declining you.

360
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,470
You mean how our parents

361
00:22:35,770 --> 00:22:37,600
wanted me to marry Sila?

362
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:40,900
I think that was...

363
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,980
a long time ago,
and it was pretty funny, too.

364
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:44,060
Not for me.

365
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,900
We were so close to Sila,

366
00:22:58,350 --> 00:22:59,840
yet he still dared to humiliate us.

367
00:23:00,060 --> 00:23:01,080
Humiliate?

368
00:23:01,870 --> 00:23:04,090
I think you're too obsessed.

369
00:23:04,830 --> 00:23:07,410
Sila did give us his reasons.

370
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:11,410
And I don't see how that tore
our relationships apart, either.

371
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,600
You know nothing, Phae.

372
00:23:15,190 --> 00:23:15,780
Right.

373
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:17,180
I don't.

374
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:19,980
And I don't wish to know anything about it.

375
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:23,490
I don't know what quarrels you had with him

376
00:23:23,630 --> 00:23:25,230
that make you two not see eye to eye.

377
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,880
But I do know I'll be staying out of this.

378
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:30,000
I want nothing to do with it.

379
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:33,920
Don't judge my relationship
with Gale based on your past.

380
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,560
I'll take my leave now.

381
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:37,840
- Phae.
- I have work to discuss with Gale.

382
00:23:38,830 --> 00:23:40,320
I'll have dinner back home.

383
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:59,210
What's with her being in such a hurry?

384
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,510
She didn't even say hi to us.

385
00:24:06,810 --> 00:24:08,980
Shall I serve the meal for you now?

386
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,440
Hey.

387
00:24:12,650 --> 00:24:14,400
What problem did you have with her this time?

388
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:17,160
She left the house looking a bit upset.

389
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:20,090
Nothing, Mom.

390
00:24:20,810 --> 00:24:21,800
What a relief.

391
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:24,770
How's the deal for Khum Rimpha going?

392
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:30,050
Everything is going according to the plan, Dad.

393
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:31,280
According to the plan?

394
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,040
Whose plan?

395
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,120
Sila's?

396
00:24:42,370 --> 00:24:44,360
There's no need for the news to reach me.

397
00:24:45,670 --> 00:24:47,120
Just go into the city,

398
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:49,510
and you'll hear the seniors talking about it.

399
00:24:50,370 --> 00:24:51,280
Right now,

400
00:24:51,770 --> 00:24:53,760
Phusangdao Farm is signing a massive deal.

401
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:55,920
And what have you been doing?

402
00:24:56,750 --> 00:24:57,620
Father,

403
00:24:57,650 --> 00:25:00,280
- I'm trying to make us...
- Make us march forward?

404
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:02,600
Enough with that phrase.

405
00:25:04,210 --> 00:25:05,520
I've heard it countless times.

406
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:10,610
If you want to become the boss,

407
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:12,360
becoming my successor...

408
00:25:15,010 --> 00:25:16,440
Sila is ahead of us.

409
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:26,680
How long must we remain his inferior?

410
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:27,920
There.

411
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:29,200
- Whoa!
- Oh!

412
00:25:29,380 --> 00:25:30,570
First-class honors? Seriously?

413
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,000
[Second-class honors]

414
00:25:41,910 --> 00:25:42,680
Hey, Muang!

415
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:45,200
Let's take pictures.

416
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:57,000
Honey.

417
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,900
I've readied my men.

418
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:06,040
You'd better do your part well.

419
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:08,360
Yes.

420
00:26:35,890 --> 00:26:36,610
Come on!

421
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:39,000
Just one more digit!

422
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:41,080
I almost

423
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,720
got to call you Big Chakkrit.

424
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:46,420
I've seen you looking at
your lottery tickets since morning.

425
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:48,360
Yet, they are all duds,

426
00:26:48,730 --> 00:26:49,480
Chakkrit.

427
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:50,880
Just give up already.

428
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:52,000
You should give up.

429
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:53,520
No, no.

430
00:26:53,610 --> 00:26:54,680
I'm not done.

431
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,560
I've got another ticket.

432
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,490
My final ticket.

433
00:27:01,990 --> 00:27:02,760
This is it!

434
00:27:02,970 --> 00:27:04,760
Alright! Alright!

435
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:09,720
Hey...

436
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:11,090
Hey...

437
00:27:12,170 --> 00:27:12,640
I won!

438
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:16,470
Won nothing!

439
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:17,230
Curses!

440
00:27:17,380 --> 00:27:18,940
- Gosh!
- No!

441
00:27:19,460 --> 00:27:20,300
Damn it!

442
00:27:21,260 --> 00:27:22,260
I almost lucked out.

443
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:37,190
See?

444
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,900
We really met before.

445
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:40,010
Remember?

446
00:27:40,870 --> 00:27:42,330
There. That was me.

447
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:43,520
And this was you.

448
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:47,180
Well...

449
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:50,680
I still can't remember meeting you there.

450
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,560
Can't you?

451
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:53,410
But...

452
00:27:53,740 --> 00:27:55,290
I remember it as clear as day.

453
00:27:55,770 --> 00:27:57,370
This was you, and that was me.

454
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:02,470
I guess I’m the only one who can remember.

455
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:06,640
It's okay if I can't

456
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,480
because right now,

457
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:10,550
we're both here

458
00:28:10,870 --> 00:28:13,100
with each other.

459
00:28:18,170 --> 00:28:19,000
Alright.

460
00:28:19,090 --> 00:28:21,610
Let me tell you about the concept
for the fashion show.

461
00:28:22,630 --> 00:28:23,820
The main idea is

462
00:28:23,850 --> 00:28:26,410
to incorporate Lanna fabric

463
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:30,160
by turning it into something of casual wear,

464
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,900
and less of special occasions.

465
00:28:33,930 --> 00:28:35,270
Why that face?

466
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:37,880
Mm...

467
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:39,990
I think..

468
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:42,610
It's still not that impressive.

469
00:28:42,730 --> 00:28:44,110
Also, the idea is not that new.

470
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:46,500
Mind you, I'm not saying it's bad.

471
00:28:46,540 --> 00:28:48,250
It's really great,

472
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,180
but...

473
00:28:50,510 --> 00:28:53,780
How about we add something to it
to make it feel more impactful?

474
00:28:54,390 --> 00:28:56,610
Mm, but how?

475
00:28:57,260 --> 00:28:58,890
Hey! How about this?

476
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,220
We use the local materials

477
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:03,040
and make Western-style patterns out of them.

478
00:29:03,550 --> 00:29:05,360
And doing this

479
00:29:05,500 --> 00:29:07,590
won't change their cultural identity.

480
00:29:07,770 --> 00:29:09,360
It's to show the whole world that

481
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:10,610
what the locals have

482
00:29:10,970 --> 00:29:13,990
can be used to create so much more than
just traditional Thai clothing.

483
00:29:15,140 --> 00:29:15,980
I believe

484
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:17,620
garments have their backgrounds.

485
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:18,690
Moreover,

486
00:29:19,330 --> 00:29:20,690
this would help us explore

487
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,390
the way of the locals here.

488
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:23,960
How does that sound?
Is it a good one?

489
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:27,720
Gale, are you paying attention?

490
00:29:28,020 --> 00:29:28,700
Mm.

491
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,150
I am.

492
00:29:30,990 --> 00:29:32,290
Well, you were giving me a weird smile.

493
00:29:33,460 --> 00:29:34,770
Your idea blew me away.

494
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,460
I've spent so much time on this,

495
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,510
yet I can't come up with an idea as cool as yours.

496
00:29:39,910 --> 00:29:41,110
You're truly amazing.

497
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:43,100
No.

498
00:29:43,370 --> 00:29:45,520
It's based on your idea.

499
00:29:45,810 --> 00:29:47,870
I simply built on it.

500
00:29:48,850 --> 00:29:49,780
In my eyes,

501
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,180
you're the best there is.

502
00:29:53,690 --> 00:29:54,490
Okay.

503
00:29:54,910 --> 00:29:57,100
Tell me how good I actually am.

504
00:29:58,790 --> 00:29:59,790
I don't know.

505
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,990
I simply think that...

506
00:30:02,370 --> 00:30:04,000
We're of the same age

507
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,990
and graduated from the same school,

508
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,610
but look at you.

509
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:10,020
You're now the owner of a massive brand.

510
00:30:10,890 --> 00:30:12,470
Meanwhile, I've got nothing for show.

511
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,940
Who says you have nothing?

512
00:30:15,390 --> 00:30:17,490
You've got Khum Rimpha.

513
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:21,340
But...

514
00:30:21,460 --> 00:30:22,960
I help run Khum Rimpha

515
00:30:23,190 --> 00:30:24,560
for the sake of my dad.

516
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:27,090
At the end of the day, it belongs to Muang.

517
00:30:27,590 --> 00:30:29,470
I have no passion for it.

518
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:32,920
It's okay.

519
00:30:33,220 --> 00:30:35,190
We're still young.

520
00:30:35,470 --> 00:30:37,640
We've still got a lot of time
to do what we love.

521
00:30:38,780 --> 00:30:40,000
But the problem is,

522
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:41,570
I don't even know

523
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:43,290
what I really love.

524
00:30:44,140 --> 00:30:46,080
Well... fashion?

525
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:47,520
Isn't that what you love?

526
00:30:48,340 --> 00:30:49,960
Back at the fashion school,

527
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:52,240
you knocked it out of the park.

528
00:31:02,410 --> 00:31:03,110
Phae.

529
00:31:04,350 --> 00:31:05,040
What's wrong?

530
00:31:07,150 --> 00:31:07,960
No, I...

531
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,320
You said

532
00:31:11,050 --> 00:31:12,100
you couldn't remember.

533
00:31:12,260 --> 00:31:14,470
So how come you're able to bring it up?

534
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:17,080
No, I...

535
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:18,350
I...

536
00:31:19,430 --> 00:31:21,000
I mean,

537
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,500
it was a guess.

538
00:31:23,390 --> 00:31:25,060
My guess was that you were at the top of the class.

539
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:28,300
FA Paris students are all talented, no?

540
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:29,280
Or am I mistaken?

541
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:36,710
Well then,

542
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,800
shall we take some selfies?

543
00:31:39,470 --> 00:31:41,710
If I forgot about you the next time we meet,

544
00:31:42,180 --> 00:31:44,280
simply show me the photos.

545
00:31:45,180 --> 00:31:47,240
Are you really going to forget about me?

546
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,320
How old are you?

547
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:50,720
Do you have Alzheimer's?

548
00:31:50,890 --> 00:31:52,920
No, it's not like that.

549
00:31:53,170 --> 00:31:54,820
It's an insurance policy

550
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:56,810
to make sure that from now on,

551
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:59,170
I'll never forget you as I did.

552
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:04,390
Okay, let's do it.

553
00:32:04,650 --> 00:32:06,520
If you forget me again,
we'll see about that.

554
00:32:13,260 --> 00:32:13,830
Did it work out?

555
00:32:14,050 --> 00:32:14,780
Let's see.

556
00:32:19,090 --> 00:32:20,920
Oh! We look so sweet in this one.

557
00:32:21,100 --> 00:32:22,060
It's so lovely.

558
00:32:22,110 --> 00:32:23,200
Can you send it over to my phone?

559
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:28,830
Uh...

560
00:32:29,490 --> 00:32:31,480
Can you send this photo to me?

561
00:32:32,510 --> 00:32:33,030
Mm.

562
00:32:34,330 --> 00:32:35,410
What's your AirDrop name?

563
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:36,890
Uh...

564
00:32:37,540 --> 00:32:39,240
It's this.

565
00:32:45,810 --> 00:32:47,670
Okay. I got it.

566
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:27,500
These kinds of tea leaves...

567
00:33:28,170 --> 00:33:29,250
What are they used for?

568
00:33:29,650 --> 00:33:31,920
Oh, the tea leaves that fell

569
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:35,720
can be used for compost or something like that.

570
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,350
But the ones that are still good

571
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:39,560
can be used for brewing tea.

572
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:42,070
This is nice. Nothing is going to waste.

573
00:33:43,540 --> 00:33:46,120
Boss came up with this idea.

574
00:33:47,810 --> 00:33:51,560
He doesn't want this to go to waste.

575
00:33:51,780 --> 00:33:52,780
You mean, Mr. Sila?

576
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:54,680
Mm, I'm talking about the boss.

577
00:33:55,630 --> 00:33:56,900
He said that

578
00:33:57,070 --> 00:33:58,870
nothing is worthless

579
00:33:58,910 --> 00:34:00,800
if we care about it.

580
00:34:07,330 --> 00:34:08,540
That's the kind of person he is?

581
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:09,400
Mm.

582
00:34:09,739 --> 00:34:10,510
If you look

583
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:14,340
deeper into him,
Boss is kind, not at all stern.

584
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:15,110
Yeah.

585
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:16,110
He...

586
00:34:16,540 --> 00:34:18,639
He takes good care

587
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,130
of the workers on the farm.

588
00:34:23,699 --> 00:34:24,940
You might be right.

589
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:32,120
The boss,
his nature is never a stern one.

590
00:34:32,159 --> 00:34:34,199
His life crumbled once.

591
00:34:34,550 --> 00:34:37,719
That's why he loves
being here on this farm.

592
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:42,370
He chose to be here?

593
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:44,770
He chose to be here

594
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:47,600
with all of us, like a family.

595
00:34:54,590 --> 00:34:55,610
What if...

596
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,840
I'm not sure if I can stay.

597
00:34:58,500 --> 00:35:00,500
If your heart
still longs to ask that question,

598
00:35:00,740 --> 00:35:02,980
that means it wants to stay, right?

599
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:09,680
Fine, fine.

600
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:12,060
Goodness, these kids!

601
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,400
They're making so much noise
playing around here again.

602
00:35:14,630 --> 00:35:15,300
Saitharn,

603
00:35:15,690 --> 00:35:16,510
carry on.

604
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:18,030
I'll be right back.

605
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,760
I'm going to shoo those little brats away.

606
00:35:21,300 --> 00:35:23,020
- Okay...
- I'll be right back.

607
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,190
[Phusangdao Group]

608
00:35:30,210 --> 00:35:33,380
Has the factory in Bangkok submitted its report
on the first half of the year?

609
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:35,890
We need their data
to write a summary for our partners.

610
00:35:36,230 --> 00:35:37,100
Not yet,

611
00:35:37,140 --> 00:35:38,930
but I've told the manager
to notify them the matter.

612
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:40,480
What's taking so long?

613
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,180
It's just a summary.

614
00:35:43,230 --> 00:35:45,150
I've told you a long time ago
to take care of this, haven't I?

615
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:48,680
Right now, the factory in Bangkok
is busy expanding its branches.

616
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:51,570
They have to coordinate with many teams,
so there's limited manpower.

617
00:35:51,900 --> 00:35:54,090
Nevertheless, please expedite it for me.

618
00:35:54,510 --> 00:35:55,910
We still have to prepare the data.

619
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:58,710
I don't want to rush that part
to avoid missing anything out.

620
00:35:59,100 --> 00:36:00,500
Yes, I'll get it sorted.

621
00:36:01,340 --> 00:36:02,280
Thank you.

622
00:36:04,130 --> 00:36:07,050
Then let's proceed
to the one with Northern Summit.

623
00:36:07,410 --> 00:36:08,110
Alright,

624
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:10,630
since the last time you asked me
to work on the timeline

625
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:12,670
to add Ms. Gale's fashion show,

626
00:36:12,790 --> 00:36:14,370
I've already discussed it with the organizer.

627
00:36:14,460 --> 00:36:17,110
They suggested it is best to place it
at the beginning of the event.

628
00:36:17,220 --> 00:36:18,920
What else did the organizer say?

629
00:36:18,940 --> 00:36:20,720
They suggested the beginning of the event

630
00:36:20,780 --> 00:36:22,640
since the stage setup, the lighting setup,

631
00:36:22,670 --> 00:36:24,720
and the attention-grabbing elements
will really help.

632
00:36:28,100 --> 00:36:29,850
If you agree,

633
00:36:29,910 --> 00:36:31,580
I will confirm it with the organizer

634
00:36:31,610 --> 00:36:32,920
and inform Ms. Gale about it as well.

635
00:36:33,330 --> 00:36:34,690
Then, it's settled.

636
00:36:35,100 --> 00:36:37,680
Please coordinate with the teams involved.

637
00:36:37,940 --> 00:36:38,600
Of course.

638
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:47,290
May I have a minute of your time?

639
00:36:47,620 --> 00:36:50,560
These are the personal items,
medications, and skincare

640
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,290
that you asked for.

641
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:53,050
Thank you.

642
00:36:56,540 --> 00:36:57,590
Skincare?

643
00:36:58,210 --> 00:36:58,800
Yes.

644
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:02,320
Chakkrit said you've accepted
someone from Bangkok to work at the farm,

645
00:37:02,380 --> 00:37:04,500
so I believe skincare is a necessity.

646
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,660
I hope you do not mind...

647
00:37:06,770 --> 00:37:08,540
that I have overprepared beyond the order.

648
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,310
Where are you going, sir?

649
00:37:19,370 --> 00:37:20,660
Deliver the skincare.

650
00:37:21,670 --> 00:37:24,200
But Mr. Sila, we haven't come
to a conclusion about the work...

651
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:28,820
What...

652
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:34,320
- Whoa!
- Woo!

653
00:37:35,310 --> 00:37:36,240
Wow!

654
00:37:36,270 --> 00:37:37,890
Vroom, vroom, vroom.

655
00:37:39,180 --> 00:37:40,010
- Wow.
- There.

656
00:37:40,100 --> 00:37:40,660
Whoa.

657
00:37:40,930 --> 00:37:42,080
After this curve,

658
00:37:42,140 --> 00:37:45,660
you'll see
the pond Saeng and I love visiting.

659
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:47,660
Okay. Whoa!

660
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,120
Hey!

661
00:37:50,820 --> 00:37:51,970
That's so freaking pretty.

662
00:37:52,750 --> 00:37:53,390
Right?

663
00:37:53,430 --> 00:37:54,310
Sure is.

664
00:37:55,580 --> 00:37:56,900
Come on, let's take a closer look.

665
00:37:56,990 --> 00:37:57,590
Where?

666
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:58,310
- Where...
- Here it is.

667
00:37:58,340 --> 00:37:59,480
Right over here.

668
00:38:00,740 --> 00:38:01,740
Wow.

669
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:03,620
Where can I put this?

670
00:38:03,650 --> 00:38:04,100
Whoa, whoa.

671
00:38:04,130 --> 00:38:05,000
- Right here...
- Right there.

672
00:38:06,090 --> 00:38:07,240
- Over there is fine.
- Okay.

673
00:38:07,270 --> 00:38:07,890
- It's good.
- Let's go.

674
00:38:07,930 --> 00:38:08,730
Come on.

675
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:10,470
I'll take you there.

676
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:11,810
Wow!

677
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,280
Whoa.

678
00:38:19,700 --> 00:38:20,610
I never knew

679
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:22,660
this kind of place existed here.

680
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:25,490
Saeng-La and I

681
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,110
always come here to hang out,

682
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:29,470
though lately,

683
00:38:30,510 --> 00:38:31,740
we barely get to visit.

684
00:38:32,390 --> 00:38:33,430
It's almost winter.

685
00:38:33,490 --> 00:38:34,490
It's almost winter.

686
00:38:35,410 --> 00:38:36,410
That's why we barely do.

687
00:38:39,310 --> 00:38:41,000
The weather here is super nice.

688
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:43,610
Just lounging around is nice enough.

689
00:38:43,890 --> 00:38:46,630
Saeng-La always
complains about the mosquitoes.

690
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:49,700
When summer arrives,

691
00:38:49,740 --> 00:38:51,300
come play with us in the water.

692
00:38:51,810 --> 00:38:52,500
It's gonna be fun.

693
00:38:53,620 --> 00:38:55,180
The summer of next year?

694
00:38:55,220 --> 00:38:55,790
Mm.

695
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,170
Scoot over.

696
00:39:03,220 --> 00:39:04,090
I don't know

697
00:39:05,500 --> 00:39:07,220
if I'm gonna be here that long.

698
00:39:08,150 --> 00:39:08,900
Who knows?

699
00:39:09,290 --> 00:39:10,970
I might've already
gone back to Bangkok by then.

700
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:12,430
What? Why?

701
00:39:12,940 --> 00:39:14,780
Are you rushing back to your partner?

702
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:22,300
You're already taken?

703
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:23,700
Ow!

704
00:39:24,190 --> 00:39:25,530
Don't be such a dumbass.

705
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:28,670
Everyone from Bangkok
is already taken.

706
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:31,990
Right, Saitharn?

707
00:39:32,350 --> 00:39:33,400
How did you guys meet?

708
00:39:33,670 --> 00:39:34,670
How long have you been together?

709
00:39:35,270 --> 00:39:36,580
Can I see their pic?

710
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:48,490
Saitharn?

711
00:39:48,830 --> 00:39:49,760
What's wrong?

712
00:39:52,330 --> 00:39:53,100
I'm...

713
00:39:53,490 --> 00:39:54,300
gonna head back first.

714
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:55,300
I want to get to bed early.

715
00:39:56,540 --> 00:39:57,500
See you tomorrow.

716
00:39:59,720 --> 00:40:00,610
Saitharn!

717
00:40:02,830 --> 00:40:04,730
Did I say something that upset him?

718
00:40:24,740 --> 00:40:25,690
What are you doing here?

719
00:40:27,490 --> 00:40:29,100
I brought you the necessities.

720
00:40:30,250 --> 00:40:31,920
A plane ticket and a cash check?

721
00:40:32,940 --> 00:40:33,410
Huh?

722
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:34,240
Right,

723
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:36,710
if that's not the case,
I wouldn't say they're necessities.

724
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:39,750
Great.

725
00:40:40,100 --> 00:40:41,100
That means they're not.

726
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:49,690
I take that back.

727
00:40:49,910 --> 00:40:50,500
No matter what,

728
00:40:50,970 --> 00:40:52,210
these are necessities.

729
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,410
Thank you, anyway.

730
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:03,880
Whoa!

731
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,660
There are so many meds here.

732
00:41:06,140 --> 00:41:07,480
I don't think
I'll go through all of these.

733
00:41:08,830 --> 00:41:11,220
I'd better give these out
to everyone tomorrow.

734
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:17,850
These are pain relief patches.

735
00:41:20,380 --> 00:41:21,650
I'll give these to Uncle Yut.

736
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:24,310
I heard him groan in pain
when he bent down.

737
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:26,300
I bet his back's in pain.

738
00:41:26,900 --> 00:41:28,080
I'll give this to Auntie Nong.

739
00:41:28,610 --> 00:41:30,350
She probably
has to be in the sun right at noon.

740
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:32,670
I don't want her to pass out.
This will be refreshing for her.

741
00:41:36,540 --> 00:41:37,840
Liniment...

742
00:41:38,710 --> 00:41:40,160
I'll give this to Paula.

743
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:43,140
She sprained her wrist.

744
00:41:43,180 --> 00:41:45,820
If left for too long,
it could get swollen.

745
00:41:47,570 --> 00:41:49,800
Here's the skincare,

746
00:41:49,830 --> 00:41:51,030
but I already have some.

747
00:41:51,700 --> 00:41:53,560
I'd better give it to Mok and Saeng.

748
00:41:53,910 --> 00:41:55,370
The boys asked me earlier,

749
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:57,150
"Why is your face so bright?
What do you use?"

750
00:41:57,550 --> 00:41:58,550
This will be perfect for them.

751
00:41:59,450 --> 00:41:59,960
Right!

752
00:42:00,870 --> 00:42:02,160
Speaking of those two,

753
00:42:03,850 --> 00:42:05,280
Mok told me

754
00:42:05,820 --> 00:42:09,070
